<div id="main">
  <h1>Social and Environmental Principles and Criteria</h1>
  <p>Here, tools, guidance and other resources are presented for the environmental elements of the UN-REDD Programmeâ€™s Social and Environmental Principles and Criteria (latest draft June 2011). These consist of 7 broad principles, within which 20 more detailed criteria describe important issues to be considered in developing REDD+ programmes.</p>
  <!-- content -->
  <div id="content">
    <h2 class="heading">All Principles</h2>
    <!-- slide-list -->
    <ul class="slide-list">
      <% @principles.each do |principle| %>
        <!-- slide-block -->
        <li class="slide-block">
        <div class="title-box">
          <a class="open" href="#">Principle <%= principle.number %></a><span><%= principle.description %></span>
        </div>
        <div class="block">
          <!-- container -->
          <div class="container">
            <% principle.criteria.each do |criterion| %>
              <!-- box -->
              <div class="box">
                <h3>Criterion <%= criterion.number %></h3>
                <p><%= criterion.description %></p>
                <div class="panel">
                  <% resource_count = criterion.resources.count %>
                  <em>There  <%= resource_count == 1 ? 'is 1 resource' : "are #{resource_count} resources" %> relating to this criteria. <%= link_to "CLICK HERE", criterion_path(criterion), :class => 'click' %></a> to see them</em>
                </div>
              </div>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        </div>
        </li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
